<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-12-17"><hi rend="italic">December 17,
                                    1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Telegram read to minister of state, who promises to urge minister for the
                            colonies, with whom I have spoken, to so rearrange Cuban tariff as to
                            secure to us the most-favored-nation treatment. Answer promised
                            soon.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>